The typescript error was coming from the guard that wraps the reconciler schedule: `Effect.flatMap(() => Effect.repeat(...))` expected an effect whose success type was `never`, but `ensureValidLimit` succeeds with `void`. I rewrote `start` to use an `Effect.gen` block that first runs the limit validation, then yields the repeating loop:

```ts
const start = (options?: StartOptions) =>
  Effect.gen(function* () {
    yield* ensureValidLimit(limit);
    return yield* Effect.repeat(iteration, schedule);
  });
```

This keeps the same behaviour—`BackfillLimitError` still short-circuits and the scheduler runs indefinitely—but the types now line up. You should no longer see the TypeScript error on that code.

